reviewText: I have been waiting for the additional series of Diagnosis Murder to be issued.  As soon as I saw them at Amazon.com, I ordered them.  Now I'm waiting for the rest of the seasons so I have the complete set.  I enjoyed these when they were on TV, and now I can enjoy them on DVD.  Thank you
Title: Diagnosis Murder: Season 5- Part Two

reviewText: It's lovable Dick Van Dyke.  Anyone who misses pure mystery entertainment that leaves you relaxed, entertained and feeds your appetite for mysteries without blood and gore, this is for you.Murder-She-Wrote fans, Father Dowling fans, Simon and Simon fans and Matlock fans really need to get the complete set of Diagnosis Murder series and have yourself a great feast for the kind of mysteries that make you feel good.
Title: Diagnosis Murder: Season 5- Part Two

reviewText: Finally!  Have been waiting for the rest of this series to become available,  Watch these old shows over & over. Beats anything on TV now!

reviewText: Great deal, excellent whodunit, Dick Van dyke if one of the greatest entertainers of all time, must watch if you want to have some fun while watching whodunits.

reviewText: season 5 is packed with stars that we all know, because we watched their shows. SEASON 5 has only 1 thing wrong with it, and that is the last show of the season. IT has part 1, then part 2, then to be continued. which means WE have to buy season 6 to find out WHO is destroying the city, WHY are they doing this ? AND even the hospital gets bombed !!!!!  I WANT SEASON 6 to get closer to finishing the series AND to find out WHO & WHY. the show is called OBSESSION.
Title: Diagnosis Murder: Season 5- Part Two

reviewText: Just be aware if you are seeking the famous scene where Doctor Sloan (Dick Van Dyke) walks past a radio station studio and sees Rob Petrie (Dick Van Dyke) - the scene has been cut from this DVD. They didn't even include it as an extra. Unbelievable!!
